  "text": "The water deficit simulated in this study provokes higher stomatal closing in the Pérola cultivar, however the more intense stomatal closing is related to smaller water content in the leaf of this cultivar and not the efficiency of the stomatal mechanism, because the leaf relative water content was smaller in the Pérola cultivar, when compared with the Pitiuba cultivar. Similar results were found by [CITATION_1] with transgenic plants of Triticum aestivum under water deficit.",
